---
title: Pan-Seared Barramundi with Shallot Butter Sauce plus Roasted Carrots & Potatoes
description: This simple, scrumptious fish dish is sure to satisfy. Mild, flaky barramundi is seasoned with salt, pepper, and Italian herbs, then pan-seared for deliciously crispy skin. A decadent, savory shallot butter sauce is spooned over the top, and the fillets are finished with sliced almonds for a crunchy, nutty finish. On the side are tender roasted carrots and onion wedges, and Italian-seasoned roasted potatoes.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/659d6fb6145e14b9dce08fa7-1f8a2432.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/659d6fb6145e14b9dce08fa7.pdf
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/pan-seared-barramundi-with-shallot-butter-sauce-659d6fb6145e14b9dce08fa7
author: Sara Heilman
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 600 kcal
  fat: 25 g
  saturated fat: 7 g
  carbohydrates: 62 g
  sugar: 16 g
  protein: 35 g
  fiber: 9 g
  sodium: 600 mg
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into ¼-inch-thick pieces. Halve and peel @onion{1}; slice into ½-inch-thick wedges. Halve @potatoes{12%ounce} lengthwise and slice into ½-inch-thick half-moons.

Toss carrots and onion wedges on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of oil, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{} (for 4 servings, arrange across entire sheet).

Toss potatoes on empty side of same baking sheet (for 4, toss potatoes on a separate sheet) with a drizzle of oil, half the @Italian seasoning{1%tbsp} (you'll use the rest later), @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. (For 4, roast carrots and onion wedges on middle rack and potatoes on top rack.)

Pat @barramundi{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with remaining Italian seasoning, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{4%tsp} in a large, preferably nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Add barramundi, skin sides down, and cook until skin is crispy, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Flip and cook until opaque and cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes} more. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Let pan cool slightly.

== Shallot Butter Sauce ==

While pan cools, halve, peel, and mince @shallot{1}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add shallot; cook, stirring, until softened and lightly browned, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add ¼ cup water, @seafood stock concentrate{1}, and @butter{1%tbsp} (1⁄3 cup water and 2 TBSP butter for 4 servings). Cook, stirring, until butter has melted and sauce has slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from heat.

== To Serve ==

Divide barramundi, carrots and onion, and potatoes between plates in separate sections.

Top barramundi with shallot butter sauce and @sliced almonds{1/2%ounce}. Serve.

> Barramundi is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.